      <p>Drag your crop box <em>inside</em> the shadow line, not on it. Sacrifice two or three millimetres of the genuine white margin if you have to. A clean white edge that's slightly smaller beats a "complete" edge with a grey halo and a fingertip in the frame. Same logic for that curved bottom corner where the page bends away from the camera and goes soft and dark. Just cut it off. Nobody reading your marksheet needs to see the curl.</p>
